<DOC><DOCNO> SJMN91-06226111 </DOCNO><ACCESS> 06226111 </ACCESS><DESCRIPT>  PROFESSIONAL; BASEBALL; GAME; RESULT; SAN-JOSE  </DESCRIPT><LEADPARA>  The San Jose Giants were looking for an edge Monday night, but they got cutdown by Modesto 1-0 in a California League game at Municipal Stadium.;   Modesto pitcher Rus Brock and reliever Will Love held the Giants to two hitsin the opening game of the series, which resumes tonight at 7:15.  </LEADPARA><SECTION>  Sports  </SECTION><HEADLINE>  MODESTO HOLDS SAN JOSE TO 2 HITS  </HEADLINE><TEXT>     The A's scored the only run of the game in the ninth. San Jose pitcherSteve Callahan threw wildly trying to pick Dean Walker off first base andWalker made it to third. He then scored on a wild pitch by Callahan.;    &quot;Idon't want to say it's a crucial series, but it's an important series becausethey're the second-place team and we could make it easier on ourselves bywinning a few games,&quot; Giants Manager Ron Wotus said.;    The Giants, who havealready secured two home playoff games by virtue of winning the NorthernDivision first half, can secure a third home game and the home-field advantagein the best-of-five series by winning the second half, which ends Aug. 28.  </TEXT><BYLINE>  Mercury News Staff Report  </BYLINE><COUNTRY>  USA  </COUNTRY><EDITION>  Stock Final  </EDITION><CODE>  SJ  </CODE><NAME>  San Jose Mercury News  </NAME><PUBDATE>   910813  </PUBDATE> <DAY>  Tuesday  </DAY><MONTH>  August  </MONTH><PG.COL>  4D  </PG.COL><PUBYEAR>  1991  </PUBYEAR><REGION>  WEST  </REGION><STATE>  CA  </STATE><WORD.CT>  179  </WORD.CT><DATELINE>  Tuesday August 13, 199100226111,SJ1  </DATELINE><COPYRGHT>  Copyright 1991, San Jose Mercury News  </COPYRGHT><LIMLEN>  1  </LIMLEN><LANGUAGE>  ENG  </LANGUAGE></DOC>